  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n#4426 introduces a new network constant which is currently not being used. \r\n\r\nI think at this point we want to keep our scoring system as is, because if a peer doesn't have blocks outside of this epoch, we still want to penalize them in order to drop them and find other peers that may have these blocks. \r\n\r\nWe could use this value to ensure that we always backfill at least up to this range, but I believe this is the case anyway. Perhaps we should use the min_epochs_for_block_requests as the epoch to which we should backfill. This way backfill can be customized at a network configuration level.\r\n",
